    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Published_EnergyComparisonReportCityWide",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to generate a city-wide energy comparison report for a specified billing period. It logs the usage of the report, calculates fiscal years, and retrieves energy consumption data along with degree day information for the specified period. The procedure aggregates CO2 emissions data and joins it with degree day information to provide a comprehensive view of energy usage and environmental impact."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple steps, including logging, fiscal year calculations, data aggregation, and joining multiple datasets. The complexity arises from the use of subqueries, joins, and the need to handle temporal data effectively."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@IsExternalUser AS CHAR(1)",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This parameter indicates whether the user is external. However, it is not utilized within the procedure, suggesting it might be intended for future use or is a placeholder."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@PublishedBillingPeriod AS VARCHAR(6)",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This parameter specifies the billing period for which the report is generated. It is crucial for filtering and joining data to ensure the report reflects the correct timeframe."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "orderedList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Logging",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure begins by logging the report usage through the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "usp_AddReportUsageLog",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " stored procedure, capturing details such as the report name and billing period."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Fiscal Year Calculation",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": It calculates the current fiscal year based on the provided billing period and determines the beginning fiscal year, which is two years prior."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Data Retrieval and Aggregation",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ":"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "listItem",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "paragraph",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "It selects data from "
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "Published.TemporalAccountLevelSummaryByCityWide",
                          "marks": [
                            {
                              "type": "code"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": ", filtering records based on the effective period and fiscal year range."
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "listItem",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "paragraph",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "A subquery aggregates CO2 emissions ("
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "co2RunningTotal",
                          "marks": [
                            {
                              "type": "code"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": ") by fiscal year, billing period, and energy type."
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "listItem",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "paragraph",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "The main query joins this aggregated data with the original dataset to include the running total of CO2 emissions."
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Degree Day Information",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure retrieves degree day information using a user-defined function "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "uftn_GetDegreeDayInformationForReporting",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and joins it with the main dataset based on the billing period."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Ordering",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The final result set is ordered by fiscal year and billing period."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Transaction Isolation Level",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The use of "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "READ UNCOMMITTED",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " can improve performance by reducing locking overhead but may lead to dirty reads."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Subquery and Joins",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The subquery for CO2 aggregation and multiple joins can be resource-intensive, especially if the datasets are large. Indexing on "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "FiscalYear",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "BillingPeriod",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "EnergyType",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " could enhance performance."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Function Calls",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The use of a scalar function for fiscal year calculation and a table-valued function for degree day information can impact performance, especially if called repeatedly for large datasets."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Potential Issues or Risks"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Dirty Reads",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "READ UNCOMMITTED",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " isolation level allows for dirty reads, which might lead to inconsistent data being reported if there are concurrent updates."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Unused Parameter",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@IsExternalUser",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " parameter is not used, which could lead to confusion or errors if developers assume it affects the procedure's logic."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Scalability",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": As data grows, the complexity of joins and subqueries may lead to performance degradation. Regular monitoring and optimization may be necessary."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Dependency on External Functions",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure relies on external functions for fiscal year calculation and degree day information, which could introduce dependencies and potential points of failure if these functions are modified or removed."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "7. Stored Procedure Definition"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "codeBlock",
      "attrs": {
        "language": "sql"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CREATE PROCEDURE [Report].[usp_Published_EnergyComparisonReportCityWide]\n(\r\n\t@IsExternalUser AS CHAR(1),\r\n\t@PublishedBillingPeriod AS VARCHAR(6)\r\n)\r\nAS\r\nBEGIN\r\n\tSET NOCOUNT ON;\r\n\tSET TRANSACTION ISOLATION LEVEL READ UNCOMMITTED;\r\n\r\n\tDECLARE @spname AS VARCHAR(100) = OBJECT_NAME(@@PROCID);\r\n\r\n\tEXEC [Audit].usp_AddReportUsageLog\r\n\t\t@ReportName\t\t\t\t\t= @spname,\r\n\t\t@StoredProcName\t\t\t\t= @spname,\r\n\t\t@RequestedBy\t\t\t\t= 'reportlog@dcas.nyc.gov',\r\n\t\t@prmPublishedBillingPeriod\t= @PublishedBillingPeriod,\r\n\t\t@prmBillingPeriod\t\t\t= NULL,\r\n\t\t@prmAgency_ies\t\t\t\t= NULL,\r\n\t\t@prmFacilityNumber_s\t\t= NULL,\r\n\t\t@prmStartingBillingPeriod\t= NULL,\r\n\t\t@prmEndingBillingPeriod\t\t= NULL;\r\n\r\n\tDECLARE @CurrentFiscalYear AS VARCHAR(4), @BeginningFiscalYear AS VARCHAR(4);\r\n\r\n\tSELECT @currentFiscalYear = [dbo].[CalculateFiscalYear](@PublishedBillingPeriod);\r\n\tSET @BeginningFiscalYear = CAST((CAST(@currentFiscalYear AS INT) - 2) AS VARCHAR);\r\n\r\n\t\r\n\tSELECT A.Seqid AS AccountLevelSummaryByCityWideSeqid,\r\n\t\t@PublishedBillingPeriod AS PublishedBillingPeriod,\r\n        A.BillingPeriod AS BillingPeriod,\r\n        A.FiscalYear,\r\n        A.EnergyType,\r\n        A.CalendarYear,\r\n        A.[MonthName],\r\n        A.MonthNameYear,\r\n        A.BilledAmount,\r\n        A.BTU,\r\n        A.CO2,\r\n\t\tT.co2RunningTotal,\r\n        A.DateAdded,\r\n        A.LastUpdate,\r\n        DD.BillingPeriod,\r\n        DD.CurrentMonthDescription,\r\n        DD.CurrentFiscalYear,\r\n        DD.PriorFiscalYear,\r\n        DD.CurrentFiscalYearBillingPeriod,\r\n        DD.CurrentMonthlyBaseCoolingDegreeDays,\r\n        DD.CurrentMonthlyBaseHeatingDegreeDays,\r\n        DD.PriorMonthlyBaseCoolingDegreeDays,\r\n        DD.PriorMonthlyBaseHeatingDegreeDays,\r\n        DD.CurrentFiscalYearBaseCoolingDegreeDays,\r\n        DD.CurrentFiscalYearBaseHeatingDegreeDays,\r\n        DD.CurrentFiscalYearNormalCoolingDegreeDays,\r\n        DD.CurrentFiscalYearNormalHeatingDegreeDays,\r\n        DD.PriorFiscalYearBillingPeriod,\r\n        DD.PriorFiscalYearBaseCoolingDegreeDays,\r\n        DD.PriorFiscalYearBaseHeatingDegreeDays,\r\n        DD.PriorFiscalYearNormalCoolingDegreeDays,\r\n        DD.PriorFiscalYearNormalHeatingDegreeDays,\r\n        DD.DeltaChangeInYearCoolingDegreeDays,\r\n        DD.DeltaChangeInYearHeatingDegreeDays\r\n\tFROM Published.TemporalAccountLevelSummaryByCityWide AS A\r\n\t\tINNER JOIN (SELECT s1.FiscalYear, s1.BillingPeriod, SUM(s2.co2) co2RunningTotal, s1.EnergyType\r\n\t\t\tFROM Published.TemporalAccountLevelSummaryByCityWide AS s1\r\n\t\t\t\tINNER JOIN Published.TemporalAccountLevelSummaryByCityWide AS s2\r\n\t\t\t\t\tON s1.FiscalYear = s2.FiscalYear AND s2.BillingPeriod <= s1.BillingPeriod AND s1.EnergyType = s2.EnergyType\r\n\t\t\tWHERE s1.EffectiveStartPeriod <= @PublishedBillingPeriod AND s1.EffectiveEndPeriod > @PublishedBillingPeriod\r\n\t\t\t\tAND s2.EffectiveStartPeriod <= @PublishedBillingPeriod AND s2.EffectiveEndPeriod > @PublishedBillingPeriod\r\n\t\t\t\tAND s1.FiscalYear BETWEEN @BeginningFiscalYear AND @CurrentFiscalYear\r\n\t\t\tGROUP BY s1.FiscalYear, s1.BillingPeriod, s1.EnergyType) AS T\r\n\t\t\tON A.FiscalYear = T.FiscalYear AND A.BillingPeriod = T.BillingPeriod AND A.EnergyType = T.EnergyType\r\n        LEFT JOIN Factors.uftn_GetDegreeDayInformationForReporting(@PublishedBillingPeriod) AS DD\r\n\t\t\tON A.BillingPeriod = DD.BillingPeriod\r\n\tWHERE A.EffectiveStartPeriod <= @PublishedBillingPeriod AND A.EffectiveEndPeriod > @PublishedBillingPeriod\r\n\t\tAND A.FiscalYear BETWEEN @BeginningFiscalYear AND @CurrentFiscalYear\r\n\tORDER BY A.FiscalYear, T.BillingPeriod;\r\nEND;"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}